{
  "//": "Default nbx-guard operator config, installed with the skill. It registers every NetBox 4.5 object type so an agent can QUERY (get/list/export/snapshot/search/resolve) the full data model out of the box. Reads only need an endpoint mapping. creatable_resources is set to [\"*\"] so `nbxg create` may make NEW objects of any registered type — but every create is still approval-gated (plan -> approve -> apply) and audited, and its rollback is a delete. UPDATE governance stays default-deny per field: only built-in low/high-risk fields are writable until you add allowed_fields / high_risk_fields yourself. Built-in types (device, interface, ip-address, prefix, vlan, contact) already work and are not repeated under extra_resources. Keep NETBOX_URL / NETBOX_TOKEN in the environment, never in this file. The installer never overwrites an existing ~/.nbx-guard/config.json; a refreshed default is saved alongside as config.json.default.",

